	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I offered a reward a while back for any of my guildmembers that could finish it.  I don't think I got any takers...  =P<BR>
In all seriousness, though, just posting a quick recap of what is known, suspected, and some of my own thoughts.<BR>
Lumi Stergnon tells you (if you have good enough faction with the Peacekeepers - if you don't, then you're never going to get it) that a staff was stolen and traced to Highkeep.<BR>
Tallus Holton drops a staff segment, and a key which yields a second segment.<BR>
Hollus Broost (sp?), who is found in one of the buildings in Kithicor (I think its the inn right next to the commons, although a female druid was there when I checked earlier today) mentions it briefly, although I don't recall specifically what he says.<BR>
Lady McCabe denies having heard anything about a staff - perhaps a little too emphatically.<BR>
<BR>
Questions arise as to how exactly it was discovered that Hoost was involved in the staff theft.  It may have been accidental, I suppose, but just hailing him doesn't yeild anything about the staff.  You need to specifically bring the topic up.<BR>
I could be wrong, but I think when I first learned of the quest (a LONG time ago), I was told that a 'HERETIC' was involved in the theft.  Heretic is an Erudite catchword for the necromancers.  Lady McCabe's casting often results in her being surrounded by a &quot;shrieking aura&quot;.<BR>
There is a persistant rumor that Lumi is supposed to give you a container (which he does not).  I don't know how this rumor started, as he does not mention anything about a container, nor does he indicate in any fashion that the staff is fragmented.<BR>
<BR>
Now for my speculations...<BR>
Lady McCabe mentions that those who dare, win.  Dunno exactly what this means, but one of the dealers on the second floor (Dealer Shoonta) makes a comment about needing a 100 plat minimum to play her table.<BR>
Of course, Isabella Cellus also speaks with Shoonta, and I have yet to hear about what Isabella is for, so Shoonta may be related to Lady McCabe's comment, Isabella's comment, both comments, or neither.<BR>
I did happen to give one hundred plat to Shoonta just to check what would happen.  Nothing did.<BR>
Of course, at this point in time, the only (non-goblin) group in Highkeep proper that doesn't like me (amiable or better) is the merchants who are all still indifferent.  I suppose if there were a way to boost faction with them, I might get a better response either with or without spending the cash.<BR>
Anyone else out there crazy enough to try this?<BR>
Has anyone given Brollus the staff segments?<BR>
Where is Aeris Graymalkin located?  The name sounds like an Erudite name, and I haven't seen this particular NPC, and yet I hear her casting all the time.  Is she located behind one of the doors that won't open?  Perhaps she is the heretic that the original conversation referred to?<BR>
Well, I hope someone can make some useful sense out of all of this.<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
